<solution>
The function <m>$f ($x )</m> is the composition, <m>$f ($x ) = $f3 ($f2 ($x ))</m>, of a quadratic function <m>$f2 ($x )=$poly </m> and power function <m>$f3 ($x2 ) = $x2 ^{ $n  }</m>.   The derivatives of these functions are <m>$f2 '($x ) = $dpoly </m> and <m>$f3 '($x2 ) = $dpower </m>.   To calculate the derivative of <m>$f ($x )</m>, we use the chain rule.
<md>
  <mrow>$f '($x )\amp = $f3 '($f2 ($x ))$f3 '($x )</mrow>
  <mrow>\amp = $f3 '($poly )($dpoly )</mrow>
  <mrow>\amp = $dpower_at_poly \left($dpoly \right)</mrow>
</md>


</solution>


